"""Terrain, sediment, sea level and rivers.

Elevation comes from Airy isostasy of the crust (thickness + density + oceanic
thermal subsidence) plus tectonic thickening, minus erosion, plus sediment.
Sea level is solved from the planet's water budget against the hypsometry, so
water-rich worlds drown and arid worlds expose vast continents.  Rivers and
flow accumulation come from real drainage routing, never from noise.
"""
